<br>
Situation: puller pulls caster mob. mob stops some ways off to cast. i pump arrows into it so it will cast at me and wait for it to finish casting. mob usually casts 3 or 4 spells before moving into melee range, then I smack it. that is how I handle casters when two boxing with my druid.<br>
<br>
is there any alternative here? some folks were asserting that getting out of visible sight of the mob (if that is possible) would cause it to move up, but I have never seen that work in my experience. it also seems that moving to the mob is not the best plan, cause that seems to increase the likelyhood of adds and does nothing to get the caster to move down to the group.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for the advice.<br>
<br>
